00:30:44.730 --> 00:31:02.650 align:middle line:90%


00:31:02.650 --> 00:31:06.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The growing consumption of
meat accelerates climate change

00:31:06.320 --> 00:31:08.900 align:middle line:90%
and species extinction.

00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:11.330 align:middle line:84%
It damages the soil,
water, and air,

00:31:11.330 --> 00:31:14.130 align:middle line:90%
and it spurs global starvation.

00:31:14.130 --> 00:31:17.090 align:middle line:84%
Appetizing, vacuum-packed
portions of meat

00:31:17.090 --> 00:31:18.440 align:middle line:90%
suggest none of this.

00:31:18.440 --> 00:31:21.150 align:middle line:90%


00:31:21.150 --> 00:31:24.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Most of the grain that's
being grown on the planet is

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:27.150 align:middle line:84%
not growing for food
for human beings.

00:31:27.150 --> 00:31:37.020 align:middle line:90%


00:31:37.020 --> 00:31:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>> We're growing plenty
of food to feed everyone.

00:31:39.760 --> 00:31:41.400 align:middle line:84%
The problem is
we're feeding most

00:31:41.400 --> 00:31:45.087 align:middle line:84%
of that grain and the legumes,
like soybeans, to animals

00:31:45.087 --> 00:31:46.170 align:middle line:90%
while people are starving.

00:31:46.170 --> 00:31:52.660 align:middle line:90%


00:31:52.660 --> 00:31:58.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Worldwide, 1.8 billion
people are starving.

00:31:58.200 --> 00:32:02.790 align:middle line:84%
Every six seconds, a child
dies of malnutrition.

00:32:02.790 --> 00:32:08.910 align:middle line:84%
That's nearly 15,000 children
a day, a sign of poverty

00:32:08.910 --> 00:32:11.175 align:middle line:84%
not for the poor,
but for the rich.

00:32:11.175 --> 00:32:14.980 align:middle line:90%


00:32:14.980 --> 00:32:20.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Only 2% of the soya in the
United States is being eaten

00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:22.010 align:middle line:90%
by human beings.

00:32:22.010 --> 00:32:25.120 align:middle line:90%
About 70% goes for animal feed.

00:32:25.120 --> 00:32:32.000 align:middle line:84%
About 28% is going for biofuel,
diesel made from soya bean.

00:32:32.000 --> 00:32:35.120 align:middle line:84%
So it's meeting the
hunger of profits,

00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:36.230 align:middle line:90%
not the hunger of people.

00:32:36.230 --> 00:32:46.900 align:middle line:90%


00:32:46.900 --> 00:32:49.410 align:middle line:84%
Corn-- about 10% of
the corn in the world

00:32:49.410 --> 00:32:51.630 align:middle line:90%
is being eaten by humans.

00:32:51.630 --> 00:32:54.300 align:middle line:84%
Most of it is going
to torture animals.

00:32:54.300 --> 00:32:57.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't say feed animals
because animals did not

00:32:57.390 --> 00:32:58.600 align:middle line:90%
want to be fed with grain.

00:32:58.600 --> 00:33:03.180 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't suit their
digestive system.

00:33:03.180 --> 00:33:05.310 align:middle line:84%
So we are talking
about a system that

00:33:05.310 --> 00:33:08.840 align:middle line:84%
is creating hunger on the planet
in the name of feeding people.

00:33:08.840 --> 00:33:15.540 align:middle line:90%


00:33:15.540 --> 00:33:19.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Currently, one out of every
three seeds of grain harvested

00:33:19.170 --> 00:33:22.580 align:middle line:84%
in the world is
used as animal feed.

00:33:22.580 --> 00:33:25.010 align:middle line:84%
However, industrial
nations can no longer

00:33:25.010 --> 00:33:28.160 align:middle line:84%
produce these huge amounts
of fodder themselves.

00:33:28.160 --> 00:33:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Thus, Europe already imports
3/4 of its animal feed,

00:33:31.970 --> 00:33:35.810 align:middle line:84%
including 35 million
tons of soybeans alone,

00:33:35.810 --> 00:33:37.843 align:middle line:90%
mainly from South America.

00:33:37.843 --> 00:33:48.000 align:middle line:90%


00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:50.130 align:middle line:84%
The land used for
growing this feed

00:33:50.130 --> 00:33:52.140 align:middle line:84%
does not consist
of empty fields,

00:33:52.140 --> 00:33:55.080 align:middle line:84%
but valuable rainforests
forced to yield

00:33:55.080 --> 00:33:58.290 align:middle line:84%
to the monocultures of the
agricultural corporations.

00:33:58.290 --> 00:34:14.889 align:middle line:90%


00:34:14.889 --> 00:34:18.865 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the really shocking
things about this desire

00:34:18.865 --> 00:34:21.569 align:middle line:84%
of more and more people to eat
more and more meat and to eat

00:34:21.569 --> 00:34:25.929 align:middle line:84%
it more and more cheaply is the
awful effect that it's having

00:34:25.929 --> 00:34:31.030 align:middle line:84%
on the environment-- so whole
forests cleared to graze

00:34:31.030 --> 00:34:35.409 align:middle line:84%
livestock or to grow
grain to feed livestock,

00:34:35.409 --> 00:34:39.340 align:middle line:84%
and it's having a shocking
effect on the environment.

00:34:39.340 --> 00:34:51.170 align:middle line:90%


00:34:51.170 --> 00:34:54.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Because of this practice,
over the past two decades,

00:34:54.590 --> 00:34:58.850 align:middle line:84%
roughly 20% of the worldwide
largest rainforests

00:34:58.850 --> 00:35:03.200 align:middle line:84%
in the Amazon basin have
been destroyed forever.

00:35:03.200 --> 00:35:06.020 align:middle line:84%
Globally, deforestation
irreversibly

00:35:06.020 --> 00:35:10.455 align:middle line:84%
destroys an area the size of a
soccer field every two seconds.

00:35:10.455 --> 00:35:18.280 align:middle line:90%


00:35:18.280 --> 00:35:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And this, although
tropical rainforests

00:35:20.410 --> 00:35:23.170 align:middle line:84%
are among the Earth's
most valuable treasures,

00:35:23.170 --> 00:35:27.340 align:middle line:84%
nowhere else is there such
a rich diversity of species.

00:35:27.340 --> 00:35:31.210 align:middle line:84%
Moreover, these forests
stabilize the world's climate

00:35:31.210 --> 00:35:34.790 align:middle line:84%
as enormous reservoirs
of carbon dioxide.

00:35:34.790 --> 00:35:37.730 align:middle line:84%
That makes them more
valuable than meat.

00:35:37.730 --> 00:35:59.735 align:middle line:90%


00:35:59.735 --> 00:36:01.890 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:01.890 --> 00:36:52.900 align:middle line:90%


00:36:52.900 --> 00:36:55.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Among the side effects of
the meat and dairy industry is

00:36:55.810 --> 00:36:58.080 align:middle line:90%
the production of methane gas.

00:36:58.080 --> 00:37:00.490 align:middle line:84%
It is primarily
generated in the stomachs

00:37:00.490 --> 00:37:02.680 align:middle line:90%
of ruminants like cattle.

00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:06.910 align:middle line:84%
Experts estimate that methane
is 25 times more detrimental

00:37:06.910 --> 00:37:08.290 align:middle line:90%
to the climate than CO2.

00:37:08.290 --> 00:37:11.570 align:middle line:90%


00:37:11.570 --> 00:37:13.550 align:middle line:84%
An even greater
concern than methane

00:37:13.550 --> 00:37:18.260 align:middle line:84%
is nitrous oxide, which
is nearly 300 times more

00:37:18.260 --> 00:37:21.170 align:middle line:90%
harmful to the climate than CO2.

00:37:21.170 --> 00:37:24.230 align:middle line:84%
It is released through the
use of synthetic fertilizers.

00:37:24.230 --> 00:37:27.710 align:middle line:90%


00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:31.220 align:middle line:84%
These and many other factors
make animal agriculture

00:37:31.220 --> 00:37:34.740 align:middle line:90%
a catalyst for climate change.

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:38.310 align:middle line:84%
There are increased reports of
a new drought of the century

00:37:38.310 --> 00:37:43.290 align:middle line:84%
or a new flood of the century,
a new storm of the century,

00:37:43.290 --> 00:37:46.385 align:middle line:84%
or the progressive melting
of the glaciers in the poles.

00:37:46.385 --> 00:37:55.680 align:middle line:90%


00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:59.250 align:middle line:84%
Intensive animal farming doesn't
just stink to high heaven.

00:37:59.250 --> 00:38:02.610 align:middle line:84%
The excrement produced is
also polluting our soil.

00:38:02.610 --> 00:38:04.800 align:middle line:84%
For each kilogram
of meat produced,

00:38:04.800 --> 00:38:08.460 align:middle line:84%
roughly 6 kilograms of
slurry are generated.

00:38:08.460 --> 00:38:10.980 align:middle line:84%
Among other things,
slurry releases

00:38:10.980 --> 00:38:13.980 align:middle line:84%
ammonia, which poisons
the surrounding air

00:38:13.980 --> 00:38:16.980 align:middle line:84%
and causes long-term
damage to the soil.

00:38:16.980 --> 00:38:24.400 align:middle line:90%


00:38:24.400 --> 00:38:27.250 align:middle line:84%
Not only that, slurry
and its nitrates

00:38:27.250 --> 00:38:30.070 align:middle line:84%
also threaten our
drinking water of which

00:38:30.070 --> 00:38:33.190 align:middle line:84%
we need inordinate amounts
to make animal products.

00:38:33.190 --> 00:38:38.220 align:middle line:90%


00:38:38.220 --> 00:38:44.580 align:middle line:84%
For 1 kilogram of eggs,
3,300 liters are needed.

00:38:44.580 --> 00:38:50.010 align:middle line:84%
For 1 kilogram of chicken
meat, 3,900 liters.

00:38:50.010 --> 00:38:54.720 align:middle line:84%
For 1 kilogram of
pork, 4,800 liters.

00:38:54.720 --> 00:39:01.850 align:middle line:84%
For 1 kilogram of cheese,
a whopping 5,000 liters.

00:39:01.850 --> 00:39:05.900 align:middle line:84%
And an all-time high
of 15,500 liters

00:39:05.900 --> 00:39:10.260 align:middle line:84%
are needed to produce
1 kilogram of beef.

00:39:10.260 --> 00:39:14.970 align:middle line:84%
Plant production has a
much better track record.

00:39:14.970 --> 00:39:21.330 align:middle line:84%
Cultivating 1 kilogram of grain
requires 1,300 liters of water.

00:39:21.330 --> 00:39:24.855 align:middle line:84%
A farmer needs just 900 liters
for a kilogram of potatoes.

00:39:24.855 --> 00:39:29.390 align:middle line:90%


00:39:29.390 --> 00:39:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And a kilogram of apples
barely requires 700 liters

00:39:33.050 --> 00:39:34.010 align:middle line:90%
of precious water.

00:39:34.010 --> 00:39:40.990 align:middle line:90%


00:39:40.990 --> 00:39:46.490 align:middle line:84%
>> This entire meat industry
has today become a scandal

00:39:46.490 --> 00:39:47.290 align:middle line:90%
on the planet.

00:39:47.290 --> 00:39:51.800 align:middle line:84%
It should not exist in the
form in which it exists.

00:39:51.800 --> 00:39:55.550 align:middle line:84%
To force everyone into
destroying the Earth's

00:39:55.550 --> 00:39:59.162 align:middle line:84%
resources is a crime
against the Earth,

00:39:59.162 --> 00:40:00.620 align:middle line:84%
and it's a crime
against our bodies

00:40:00.620 --> 00:40:03.180 align:middle line:84%
because our bodies weren't
designed for this kind of diet.

00:40:03.180 --> 00:40:08.090 align:middle line:90%


00:40:08.090 --> 00:40:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Altogether, this is a recipe
for biological disaster,

00:40:13.220 --> 00:40:17.580 align:middle line:84%
biodiversity disaster, water
disaster, climate disaster,

00:40:17.580 --> 00:40:18.380 align:middle line:90%
health disaster.

00:40:18.380 --> 00:40:21.260 align:middle line:90%


00:40:21.260 --> 00:40:46.470 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:40:46.470 --> 00:40:49.590 align:middle line:84%
>> We were made to believe that
meat-based diets are superior

00:40:49.590 --> 00:40:53.010 align:middle line:84%
to plant-based diets, a lie
that has been exposed by medical

00:40:53.010 --> 00:40:57.120 align:middle line:84%
experts again and
again and again.

00:40:57.120 --> 00:40:59.160 align:middle line:90%
So what do we need to do?

00:40:59.160 --> 00:41:03.240 align:middle line:84%
We need to bring diversity
back into our farms.

00:41:03.240 --> 00:41:06.470 align:middle line:84%
We need to bring harmony
back into our farms.

00:41:06.470 --> 00:41:08.410 align:middle line:90%
We have to celebrate diversity.

00:41:08.410 --> 00:41:09.840 align:middle line:90%
We have to work with farmers.

00:41:09.840 --> 00:41:11.007 align:middle line:90%
We have to know our farmers.

00:41:11.007 --> 00:41:19.880 align:middle line:90%


00:41:19.880 --> 00:41:22.200 align:middle line:84%
We have to start
realizing food is

00:41:22.200 --> 00:41:24.090 align:middle line:90%
what keeps the world's going.

00:41:24.090 --> 00:41:26.520 align:middle line:90%
Food is the energy of the world.

00:41:26.520 --> 00:41:29.940 align:middle line:84%
And we have to know
exactly where in that chain

00:41:29.940 --> 00:41:35.040 align:middle line:84%
we entered so that we don't do
more harm, we reduce the harm,

00:41:35.040 --> 00:41:37.950 align:middle line:84%
and, in the process,
we celebrate.

00:41:37.950 --> 00:41:40.170 align:middle line:90%
Food is life, and life is food.

00:41:40.170 --> 00:41:46.070 align:middle line:90%


00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Through its way of life,
the Langerhorst family in Upper

00:41:48.860 --> 00:41:52.990 align:middle line:84%
Austria exemplifies the practice
of farming without monocultures

00:41:52.990 --> 00:41:55.340 align:middle line:90%
and intensive animal husbandry.

00:41:55.340 --> 00:41:57.410 align:middle line:84%
It's been running a
vegan organic farm

00:41:57.410 --> 00:41:59.450 align:middle line:84%
with mixed cultivation
and permaculture

00:41:59.450 --> 00:42:01.550 align:middle line:90%
for more than 40 years.

00:42:01.550 --> 00:42:05.030 align:middle line:84%
The family grows vegetables,
fruit, berries, and nuts,

00:42:05.030 --> 00:42:08.090 align:middle line:84%
and avoids animal-based
and chemical fertilizers,

00:42:08.090 --> 00:42:12.620 align:middle line:84%
using green manure, plant-based
compost, rock flour, mulch,

00:42:12.620 --> 00:42:13.550 align:middle line:90%
and wood ash.

00:42:13.550 --> 00:42:19.446 align:middle line:90%


00:42:19.446 --> 00:42:47.150 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:42:47.150 --> 00:43:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:43:19.370 --> 00:43:21.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Nature shows us how
to solve our problems,

00:43:21.980 --> 00:43:24.530 align:middle line:84%
our personal problems and the
ones that involve the whole

00:43:24.530 --> 00:43:25.330 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:43:25.330 --> 00:43:27.420 align:middle line:90%


00:43:27.420 --> 00:43:28.880 align:middle line:90%
We just need to take action.

00:43:28.880 --> 00:43:33.560 align:middle line:90%


00:43:33.560 --> 00:43:38.720 align:middle line:84%
>> If we look at the
chances according to human

00:43:38.720 --> 00:43:41.660 align:middle line:84%
possibilities,
human intelligence,

00:43:41.660 --> 00:43:45.410 align:middle line:84%
human longing for
good, decent food,

00:43:45.410 --> 00:43:49.490 align:middle line:84%
I think the chances are
extremely high that we can all

00:43:49.490 --> 00:43:53.930 align:middle line:84%
live on a good, healthy,
organic, plant-based diet.

00:43:53.930 --> 00:44:24.600 align:middle line:90%


00:44:24.600 --> 00:44:27.450 align:middle line:84%
>> We love the notion
of romantic rural life,

00:44:27.450 --> 00:44:31.260 align:middle line:84%
happy animals and a healthy
environment well provided

00:44:31.260 --> 00:44:33.130 align:middle line:90%
for by Mother Nature.

00:44:33.130 --> 00:44:36.930 align:middle line:84%
It's really quite tempting to
get this meat on your plate.

00:44:36.930 --> 00:44:38.655 align:middle line:90%
But let's face reality.

00:44:38.655 --> 00:44:47.030 align:middle line:90%


00:44:47.030 --> 00:44:49.030 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:44:49.030 --> 00:45:09.100 align:middle line:90%


00:45:09.100 --> 00:45:12.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Meat is less expensive
today than ever before,

00:45:12.250 --> 00:45:13.870 align:middle line:90%
a cheap product.

00:45:13.870 --> 00:45:17.170 align:middle line:84%
About 98% comes
from factory farms

00:45:17.170 --> 00:45:20.560 align:middle line:84%
where conditions are
beyond imagination.

00:45:20.560 --> 00:45:24.190 align:middle line:84%
Rarely in the past has the
term "industry" smacked

00:45:24.190 --> 00:45:29.270 align:middle line:84%
of a contempt for life
as it does to day.

00:45:29.270 --> 00:45:55.340 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:45:55.340 --> 00:45:58.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Chickens are, by
nature, social, curious,

00:45:58.940 --> 00:46:00.920 align:middle line:90%
and intelligent animals.

00:46:00.920 --> 00:46:03.290 align:middle line:84%
But in the merciless
factory farm,

00:46:03.290 --> 00:46:10.410 align:middle line:84%
their lives are reduced to
short and joyless agony.

00:46:10.410 --> 00:46:14.250 align:middle line:84%
Chicks hatch not in the maternal
nest but in the incubator.

00:46:14.250 --> 00:46:18.120 align:middle line:84%
As soon as they can stand,
they are sorted, vaccinated,

00:46:18.120 --> 00:46:21.225 align:middle line:84%
packed up, and sent
to enormous feedlots.

00:46:21.225 --> 00:46:28.770 align:middle line:90%


00:46:28.770 --> 00:46:32.340 align:middle line:84%
In these animal prisons, they
reach slaughtering weight

00:46:32.340 --> 00:46:35.760 align:middle line:84%
in record time,
never seeing daylight

00:46:35.760 --> 00:46:38.650 align:middle line:84%
and under extremely
crowded conditions.

00:46:38.650 --> 00:46:47.240 align:middle line:90%


00:46:47.240 --> 00:46:51.140 align:middle line:84%
The normal life expectancy
of a chicken is 20 years.

00:46:51.140 --> 00:46:54.950 align:middle line:84%
Broilers is only
live up to 42 days.

00:46:54.950 --> 00:46:59.690 align:middle line:84%
During this brief lifespan, they
must gain roughly 2 kilograms.

00:46:59.690 --> 00:47:03.490 align:middle line:84%
No organism can withstand
such brutally rapid growth.

00:47:03.490 --> 00:47:09.700 align:middle line:90%


00:47:09.700 --> 00:47:50.000 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:53.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Some animals don't
survive this abnormal growth.

00:47:53.240 --> 00:47:57.110 align:middle line:84%
They can't drag themselves to
the feed and water troughs.

00:47:57.110 --> 00:48:01.550 align:middle line:84%
Others die of breeding-induced
cardiovascular diseases.

00:48:01.550 --> 00:48:05.240 align:middle line:84%
They succumb to stress or
fall victim to cannibalism.

00:48:05.240 --> 00:48:16.470 align:middle line:90%


00:48:16.470 --> 00:48:20.310 align:middle line:84%
All these are facts we are often
not aware of when eating meat

00:48:20.310 --> 00:48:23.490 align:middle line:84%
and which the meat lobby
is glad to keep concealed.

00:48:23.490 --> 00:48:35.620 align:middle line:90%


00:48:35.620 --> 00:48:37.510 align:middle line:90%
This is a mother sow.

00:48:37.510 --> 00:48:40.840 align:middle line:84%
This highly intelligent
and extremely sensitive

00:48:40.840 --> 00:48:44.410 align:middle line:84%
animal spends most of
its life in crates,

00:48:44.410 --> 00:48:48.370 align:middle line:84%
in cages hardly any
larger than themselves.

00:48:48.370 --> 00:48:51.220 align:middle line:84%
Instead of straw, they
lie on bare concrete.

00:48:51.220 --> 00:48:54.280 align:middle line:90%


00:48:54.280 --> 00:48:56.470 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:48:56.470 --> 00:49:28.140 align:middle line:90%


00:49:28.140 --> 00:49:30.750 align:middle line:84%
>> In nature, mother
sows build big,

00:49:30.750 --> 00:49:33.750 align:middle line:90%
soft nests for their offspring.

00:49:33.750 --> 00:49:37.090 align:middle line:84%
On factory farms, however,
this isn't possible.

00:49:37.090 --> 00:49:41.190 align:middle line:84%
The sows farrow in
gestation crates.

00:49:41.190 --> 00:49:44.890 align:middle line:84%
Confined, they are neither
able to protect nor care

00:49:44.890 --> 00:49:45.690 align:middle line:90%
for their young.

00:49:45.690 --> 00:50:05.060 align:middle line:90%


00:50:05.060 --> 00:50:07.850 align:middle line:84%
Not long after birth,
the piglets' tails

00:50:07.850 --> 00:50:11.540 align:middle line:84%
are docked as a precaution
against cannibalism.

00:50:11.540 --> 00:50:14.360 align:middle line:84%
In addition, male
piglets are castrated

00:50:14.360 --> 00:50:18.980 align:middle line:84%
by ripping out their testicles,
everything without pain relief

00:50:18.980 --> 00:50:21.680 align:middle line:84%
