01:10:52.980 --> 01:10:55.240 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:10:55.240 --> 01:11:20.860 align:middle line:90%


01:11:20.860 --> 01:11:46.470 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:11:46.470 --> 01:11:50.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Everyone is aware that
animals have to die if we want

01:11:50.100 --> 01:11:54.330 align:middle line:84%
to eat meat, but very few want
to know what actually takes

01:11:54.330 --> 01:11:56.160 align:middle line:90%
place in a slaughterhouse.

01:11:56.160 --> 01:11:58.350 align:middle line:84%
Slaughterhouses
have their reasons

01:11:58.350 --> 01:12:00.990 align:middle line:90%
for not welcoming visitors.

01:12:00.990 --> 01:12:02.970 align:middle line:84%
In large industrial
slaughterhouses,

01:12:02.970 --> 01:12:05.190 align:middle line:84%
pigs are often
stunned by machine.

01:12:05.190 --> 01:12:09.360 align:middle line:84%
An electric shock triggers
a kind of epileptic attack.

01:12:09.360 --> 01:12:12.680 align:middle line:90%
This leads to unconsciousness.

01:12:12.680 --> 01:12:15.650 align:middle line:84%
In smaller operations,
stunning by electric current

01:12:15.650 --> 01:12:18.530 align:middle line:84%
is generally done by hand
before the animals are

01:12:18.530 --> 01:12:21.350 align:middle line:84%
suspended from a conveyor
and their throats slashed.

01:12:21.350 --> 01:12:23.960 align:middle line:90%


01:12:23.960 --> 01:12:26.190 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:12:26.190 --> 01:13:03.700 align:middle line:90%


01:13:03.700 --> 01:13:07.660 align:middle line:84%
>> In large meat factories, gas
chambers are standard practice.

01:13:07.660 --> 01:13:09.940 align:middle line:84%
The pigs are herded
into a gondola

01:13:09.940 --> 01:13:12.040 align:middle line:84%
and lowered into a
chamber where they

01:13:12.040 --> 01:13:15.340 align:middle line:84%
are gassed with a mixture
of carbon dioxide and air,

01:13:15.340 --> 01:13:16.620 align:middle line:90%
leaving them unconscious.

01:13:16.620 --> 01:13:21.640 align:middle line:90%


01:13:21.640 --> 01:13:45.450 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:13:45.450 --> 01:14:15.040 align:middle line:90%


01:14:15.040 --> 01:14:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Once they have been stunned,
the pigs' throats must be

01:14:17.740 --> 01:14:20.200 align:middle line:84%
quickly and properly
slashed, otherwise,

01:14:20.200 --> 01:14:23.140 align:middle line:84%
the animals wake up and land in
the cauldron of boiling water

01:14:23.140 --> 01:14:24.470 align:middle line:90%
fully conscious.

01:14:24.470 --> 01:14:27.700 align:middle line:84%
This is no uncommon occurrence
since the whole process

01:14:27.700 --> 01:14:30.850 align:middle line:90%
takes place so quickly.

01:14:30.850 --> 01:14:32.600 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:14:32.600 --> 01:15:25.310 align:middle line:90%


01:15:25.310 --> 01:15:27.260 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:15:27.260 --> 01:15:54.880 align:middle line:90%


01:15:54.880 --> 01:15:57.490 align:middle line:90%
>> All pigs can meet this fate.

01:15:57.490 --> 01:16:00.680 align:middle line:84%
Animals from organic
farms are no exception.

01:16:00.680 --> 01:16:06.530 align:middle line:90%


01:16:06.530 --> 01:16:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Once it is cut into
pieces, the animal

01:16:08.450 --> 01:16:10.430 align:middle line:84%
has finally endured
all the agony

01:16:10.430 --> 01:16:11.630 align:middle line:90%
the industry has to offer.

01:16:11.630 --> 01:16:24.620 align:middle line:90%


01:16:24.620 --> 01:16:27.200 align:middle line:84%
Chickens are processed
fully automatically

01:16:27.200 --> 01:16:28.820 align:middle line:90%
and at a high speed.

01:16:28.820 --> 01:16:31.400 align:middle line:84%
On average, 10,000
animals per hour

01:16:31.400 --> 01:16:35.330 align:middle line:84%
can be stunned, killed,
cleaned, and cut into parts

01:16:35.330 --> 01:16:37.233 align:middle line:90%
in a modern slaughterhouse.

01:16:37.233 --> 01:16:40.690 align:middle line:90%


01:16:40.690 --> 01:16:44.170 align:middle line:84%
Europe's largest poultry
slaughterhouse is in Germany.

01:16:44.170 --> 01:16:47.830 align:middle line:84%
It can handle up to
27,000 animals an hour.

01:16:47.830 --> 01:17:02.580 align:middle line:90%
That's 432,000 chickens a day.

01:17:02.580 --> 01:17:06.270 align:middle line:84%
The slaughter of cattle starts
with a captive bolt stunner,

01:17:06.270 --> 01:17:08.940 align:middle line:84%
which has been standard
procedure for decades.

01:17:08.940 --> 01:17:12.960 align:middle line:84%
The animals are driven along
a chute into a narrow box.

01:17:12.960 --> 01:17:15.880 align:middle line:84%
Not every animal goes
to its death willingly.

01:17:15.880 --> 01:17:28.030 align:middle line:90%


01:17:28.030 --> 01:18:00.650 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:18:00.650 --> 01:18:39.170 align:middle line:90%


01:18:39.170 --> 01:19:24.112 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:19:24.112 --> 01:19:56.140 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:19:56.140 --> 01:19:58.135 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:19:58.135 --> 01:20:47.310 align:middle line:90%


01:20:47.310 --> 01:20:50.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Humans are creatures
with many contradictions.

01:20:50.790 --> 01:20:55.320 align:middle line:84%
What is especially paradoxical
is our relationship to animals.

01:20:55.320 --> 01:20:58.290 align:middle line:84%
We can adore a pet,
and, at the same time,

01:20:58.290 --> 01:21:01.560 align:middle line:84%
we let other animals be
killed without the slightest

01:21:01.560 --> 01:21:03.150 align:middle line:90%
compassion.

01:21:03.150 --> 01:21:08.600 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Melanie Joy calls
this phenomena carnism.

01:21:08.600 --> 01:21:12.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Carnism teaches us to
place animals in categories

01:21:12.280 --> 01:21:13.450 align:middle line:90%
in our minds.

01:21:13.450 --> 01:21:14.950 align:middle line:90%
Some animals we love.

01:21:14.950 --> 01:21:17.440 align:middle line:84%
Dogs and cats are our
companions, our family members,

01:21:17.440 --> 01:21:19.120 align:middle line:90%
our friends, for instance.

01:21:19.120 --> 01:21:22.180 align:middle line:90%
Other animals we eat.

01:21:22.180 --> 01:21:24.970 align:middle line:84%
Carnism teaches us to
see animals as objects.

01:21:24.970 --> 01:21:30.070 align:middle line:84%
So we learn to refer to
the turkey on our plate

01:21:30.070 --> 01:21:32.830 align:middle line:84%
as something rather
than someone.

01:21:32.830 --> 01:21:35.650 align:middle line:84%
And carnism teaches us to
see animals as abstractions,

01:21:35.650 --> 01:21:38.860 align:middle line:84%
as lacking in any individuality
or personality of their own

01:21:38.860 --> 01:21:42.670 align:middle line:84%
and, instead, simply as
abstract members of a group

01:21:42.670 --> 01:21:45.850 align:middle line:84%
about which we've made
generalized assumptions.

01:21:45.850 --> 01:21:48.260 align:middle line:84%
A pig is a pig, and
all pigs are the same.

01:21:48.260 --> 01:21:52.060 align:middle line:90%


01:21:52.060 --> 01:21:55.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Carnism, says Dr. Joy,
is a belief system intended

01:21:55.660 --> 01:22:00.280 align:middle line:84%
to prevent us from recognizing
the violence and cruelty

01:22:00.280 --> 01:22:03.310 align:middle line:84%
of the system behind
eating animals.

01:22:03.310 --> 01:22:05.410 align:middle line:90%
We suppress and deny.

01:22:05.410 --> 01:22:09.040 align:middle line:84%
We ignore our head and our
heart when it comes to animals

01:22:09.040 --> 01:22:11.005 align:middle line:90%
that we classify as edible.

01:22:11.005 --> 01:22:14.810 align:middle line:90%


01:22:14.810 --> 01:22:19.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Choosing one animal to eat
and one animal to be a pet is

01:22:19.110 --> 01:22:20.070 align:middle line:90%
just--

01:22:20.070 --> 01:22:21.480 align:middle line:90%
some people call it speciesism.

01:22:21.480 --> 01:22:25.190 align:middle line:84%
It's just-- it's
a kind of racism.

01:22:25.190 --> 01:22:27.240 align:middle line:90%
It's a kind of favoritism.

01:22:27.240 --> 01:22:32.430 align:middle line:84%
And it's a kind of just
following a particular culture.

01:22:32.430 --> 01:22:36.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, what we have
to do is we have

01:22:36.080 --> 01:22:38.570 align:middle line:84%
to build a culture
and traditions based

01:22:38.570 --> 01:22:39.560 align:middle line:90%
upon compassion.

01:22:39.560 --> 01:22:58.630 align:middle line:90%


01:22:58.630 --> 01:23:02.770 align:middle line:84%
>> The highest form of
living, the highest value,

01:23:02.770 --> 01:23:04.720 align:middle line:90%
is compassion.

01:23:04.720 --> 01:23:08.680 align:middle line:84%
And when there is compassion,
we maximize well-being.

01:23:08.680 --> 01:23:12.700 align:middle line:84%
After all, the word "wealth"
comes from well-being.

01:23:12.700 --> 01:23:15.730 align:middle line:84%
It did not mean money
in the hands of a few.

01:23:15.730 --> 01:23:20.400 align:middle line:84%
It meant well-being shared
across life spectrum.

01:23:20.400 --> 01:23:52.690 align:middle line:90%


01:23:52.690 --> 01:23:56.770 align:middle line:84%
>> I think once we admit that we
humans are not the only beings

01:23:56.770 --> 01:23:59.410 align:middle line:84%
with personalities,
minds, and feelings,

01:23:59.410 --> 01:24:03.340 align:middle line:84%
once we realize that we are
part of the animal kingdom,

01:24:03.340 --> 01:24:07.850 align:middle line:84%
then it becomes quite as
important how we treat animals,

01:24:07.850 --> 01:24:11.230 align:middle line:84%
all animals, as how
we treat each other.

01:24:11.230 --> 01:24:16.990 align:middle line:84%
And so only when we show respect
and consideration and concern

01:24:16.990 --> 01:24:20.260 align:middle line:84%
for other living
beings can we imagine

01:24:20.260 --> 01:24:22.780 align:middle line:84%
a world that's more
peaceful than the one today.

01:24:22.780 --> 01:24:43.760 align:middle line:90%


01:24:43.760 --> 01:24:47.060 align:middle line:84%
>> We are at a threshold where
across the world people are

01:24:47.060 --> 01:24:51.620 align:middle line:84%
seeking the liberation of
life from this stranglehold

01:24:51.620 --> 01:24:56.780 align:middle line:84%
of objectification, the view
that the Earth is dead matter

01:24:56.780 --> 01:24:59.330 align:middle line:90%
and our beings are just objects.

01:24:59.330 --> 01:25:02.750 align:middle line:84%
We have to rise in subject
to it, of an interconnected

01:25:02.750 --> 01:25:04.490 align:middle line:90%
subject to it.

01:25:04.490 --> 01:25:07.670 align:middle line:84%
No life is less important
than any other life,

01:25:07.670 --> 01:25:11.120 align:middle line:84%
and human beings are
definitely not the emperors

01:25:11.120 --> 01:25:12.960 align:middle line:90%
over the rest of life--

01:25:12.960 --> 01:25:16.070 align:middle line:84%
are just one strand
in that web of life.

01:25:16.070 --> 01:25:33.860 align:middle line:90%


01:25:33.860 --> 01:25:36.580 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the reason that
so many people don't change

01:25:36.580 --> 01:25:39.950 align:middle line:84%
their behavior is because
they feel, what's the use?

01:25:39.950 --> 01:25:42.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm just one person,
so what I do actually

01:25:42.160 --> 01:25:45.310 align:middle line:84%
can't make any difference,
and nor would it

01:25:45.310 --> 01:25:47.410 align:middle line:84%
make any difference
if it was just one.

01:25:47.410 --> 01:25:56.890 align:middle line:90%


01:25:56.890 --> 01:25:58.960 align:middle line:84%
But more and more
and more people

01:25:58.960 --> 01:26:02.140 align:middle line:84%
are coming to understand
what the problems are

01:26:02.140 --> 01:26:03.700 align:middle line:90%
and what they ought to be doing.

01:26:03.700 --> 01:26:15.250 align:middle line:90%


01:26:15.250 --> 01:26:21.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Never, ever think that one
person can't make a difference.

01:26:21.990 --> 01:26:26.300 align:middle line:84%
We tend to focus our energies
on looking for leaders,

01:26:26.300 --> 01:26:29.540 align:middle line:84%
say, like Martin Luther
King or Mahatma Gandhi.

01:26:29.540 --> 01:26:32.310 align:middle line:90%


01:26:32.310 --> 01:26:34.920 align:middle line:90%
But they were just one person.

01:26:34.920 --> 01:26:38.300 align:middle line:84%
They didn't set out in
life to be a leader,

01:26:38.300 --> 01:26:41.730 align:middle line:84%
and they were very
humble people.

01:26:41.730 --> 01:26:48.530 align:middle line:84%
It's just that circumstances in
history drew them to the front.

01:26:48.530 --> 01:26:51.350 align:middle line:84%
But if we're looking for
leaders, all we have to do

01:26:51.350 --> 01:26:54.530 align:middle line:84%
is go home and look in the
mirror because each one of us

01:26:54.530 --> 01:26:57.980 align:middle line:84%
can make a
difference, and we do.

01:26:57.980 --> 01:27:01.010 align:middle line:84%
It's just making a
conscious decision

01:27:01.010 --> 01:27:04.290 align:middle line:84%
that we are going to make
a difference in our lives.

01:27:04.290 --> 01:27:07.040 align:middle line:84%
We're not on this
planet for a long time,

01:27:07.040 --> 01:27:10.010 align:middle line:84%
so we need to do what
we can in the time we've

01:27:10.010 --> 01:27:12.096 align:middle line:90%
got to make a difference.

01:27:12.096 --> 01:27:43.500 align:middle line:90%


01:27:43.500 --> 01:28:30.220 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:28:30.220 --> 01:28:33.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Every one of us
can make a difference.

01:28:33.210 --> 01:28:37.340 align:middle line:84%
Every one of us eats at least
two to three times a day.

01:28:37.340 --> 01:28:40.550 align:middle line:84%
And every act of
conscious eating,

01:28:40.550 --> 01:28:42.860 align:middle line:84%
of knowing what the
consequences of your eating

01:28:42.860 --> 01:28:46.160 align:middle line:84%
are, knowing what
you're eating is

01:28:46.160 --> 01:28:48.350 align:middle line:90%
an act of changing the world.

01:28:48.350 --> 01:29:19.460 align:middle line:90%


01:29:19.460 --> 01:29:24.110 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the most important
message that I have is

01:29:24.110 --> 01:29:29.240 align:middle line:84%
to remember that you-- and I'm
speaking to you watching this

01:29:29.240 --> 01:29:30.050 align:middle line:90%
film--

01:29:30.050 --> 01:29:31.250 align:middle line:90%
you make a difference.

01:29:31.250 --> 01:29:33.650 align:middle line:84%
You as an individual
make a difference.

01:29:33.650 --> 01:29:37.280 align:middle line:84%
What you do each day
actually is affecting what's

01:29:37.280 --> 01:29:39.680 align:middle line:90%
going on in the world each day.

01:29:39.680 --> 01:29:41.870 align:middle line:90%
So your life matters.

01:29:41.870 --> 01:29:43.130 align:middle line:90%
You matter.

01:29:43.130 --> 01:29:44.900 align:middle line:90%
And use your life work wisely.

01:29:44.900 --> 01:29:47.600 align:middle line:90%


01:29:47.600 --> 01:29:50.950 align:middle line:90%
